article.headline: Yale 80, Harvard 62
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Edwin Draughan scored 17 points on 7-of-10 shooting to lead Yale to an 80-62 win over Harvard on Friday. The Bulldogs (10-14, 5-6 Ivy League) shot 60 percent in the first half and built a 44-31 lead at the break. Alex Gamboa had four of Yale's 13 steals and led the team with six boards. The Crimson (4-20, 3-8) committed 23 turnovers and it cost them. Yale scored 29 points off the miscues. The Bulldogs dominated inside, outrebounding Harvard 36-28 and finishing with a 40-26 scoring edge in the paint. Dominick Martin added 13 points and five boards for Yale. David Giovacchini led the Crimson with 15 points. Teammate Matt Stehle finished with 14 points and nine rebounds.
